      "content": "It's completely understandable to feel this way given the significant changes being imposed. However, let's not underestimate the power of innovation, even with limitations. We may have to rethink our narrative strategies and perhaps introduce subtler ways to incorporate complex themes. It won't be the same as before, but it's not necessarily a downgrade in quality. We can still create compelling narratives, even with cardboard characters, by focusing on their depth in other ways. Let's look at this as an opportunity to explore new dimensions of writing that we haven't considered before.",
